JAVA COURSE

to show input/output terminal, take input/output from a user without using Scanner
but instead a terminal:

// library of the class
import javax.swing.JOptionPane;

public class tring
{
    public static void main(String args[])
    {
        //JOption.showInputDialog();
        String name = JOptionPane.showInputDialog("entrt ur name");
        // for output
        //JOption.showMessageDialog();
        JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null."hello "+name);

        // initializing and declaring datatype
        // used for any data type accordingly
        int age=Integer.pareInt(JOptionPane.showInputDialog("enter ut age"));
        JOptionPane.showMessageDialog(null,"you are "+age+" years ols");
    }
}



toString() = special method that all objects inherit
             that returns a String that can "textually represent" an object
             can be used both implicitly or explicitly
             // to return all of the attributes of the object


ARRAY OF OBJECTS:

public class food
{
    String name;

    food(String name)
    {
        this.name=name;
    }

    public static void main(String args[])
    {
        food[] rf = new food[3];

        food food1 = new food("pizza");
        food food2 = new food("cereal");
        food food3 = new food("burger");

        rf[0]=food1;
        rf[1]=food2;
        rf[3]=food3;

        System.out.println(rf[0]);
        // this gives the addres of the first element of the array

        System.out.prnitln(rf[0].name);
        // this gives the element in the first index -> pizza

        System.out.prnitln(rf[1].name);
        System.out.prnitln(rf[2].name);

    }
}


